    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d176">
                <head>No. 176.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">Edward
                                        Thornton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30,
                                        1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to state that this
                                Department is informed by a letter of 29th instant, from the Acting
                                Secretary of the Navy, that instructions have been sent to Commander
                                Byron Wilson, commanding the United States steamer Yantic, to
                                co-operate with Sir II. B. E. Frere, the agent of Her Britannic
                                Majesty’s government, in any proper way to secure the success of his
                                mission to Muscat or Zanzibar.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
